# Component Structure

## Hooks + Components Pattern

Separate logic from UI:

- **Hook** (`hooks/useFeature.js`): logic, data fetching, translations, state, side effects
- **Component** (`components/Feature/Feature.jsx`): calls the hook and renders UI, or delegates to a View component
- **Page** (`pages/FeaturePage.jsx`): composes components with per-page SEO via `usePageSEO`

Extracting a separate View component is optional. Use your judgment -- if a component is small, a single file is fine.

## Shared Atoms

Reusable UI primitives live in `components/atoms/`:

- `SectionHeader` -- tag + title + ornament
- `BookingButton` -- booking CTA link
- `RatingBadge` -- Google rating display

## Code Splitting

- `HomePage` is eagerly loaded (landing page)
- All other pages use `React.lazy` + `Suspense`
- Three.js CDN scripts are conditionally loaded only on desktop (width > 768)

## SEO Requirement

Every page must call `usePageSEO` with translated `title` and `description` from `translations.seo`.

## File Structure

```
src/
  components/
    atoms/              <- shared reusable atoms
    Feature/
      Feature.jsx       <- component (may contain logic or delegate to View)
      FeatureView.jsx   <- optional pure UI component
  hooks/
    useFeature.js       <- logic + data
  pages/
    FeaturePage.jsx     <- page composition + SEO
  contexts/             <- React contexts
  data/                 <- static data (images, services, reviews)
  lib/                  <- non-React utilities (slider)
  translations/         <- i18n strings
```
